{{Infobox software | name = Adobe Fuse CC | logo = | logo caption = | logo size = | logo alt = | screenshot = | caption = | screenshot size = | screenshot alt = | collapsible = | author = Mixamo | developer = Adobe Systems | released = {{Start date and age|2014|03|27|df=yes}} | discontinued = | latest release version = 1.2 | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2014|08|07|df=yes}} | operating system = Mac OSX 10.8 or Win 7 and later | language = [[English language|English]] | website = {{URL|https://www.mixamo.com/fuse}} | AsOf = November 2014 }}
'''Adobe Fuse CC''' (formerly '''Fuse Character Creator''') is a [[3D computer graphics]] software developed by [[Mixamo]] that enables users to create 3D characters. Its main novelty is the ability to import and integrate user generated content into the character creator.<ref name=digitalmedia>{{cite news|title=Mixamo Opens Character Customization to User-Imported Content |date=November 30, 2011 |publisher=Digital Media World |url=http://digitalmedia-world.com/Games/mixamo-opens-character-customization-to-user-imported-content.html |accessdate=November 23, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150320070657/http://digitalmedia-world.com/Games/mixamo-opens-character-customization-to-user-imported-content.html |archivedate=March 20, 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref name=gamasutra>{{cite news |title=Fuse character modelling tech receives more advanced customization |author=Mike Rose |date=May 21, 2014 |publisher=Gamasutra |url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/218084/Fuse_character_modelling_tech_receives_more_advanced_customization.php |accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref> Fuse is part of Mixamo's product suite and it is aimed at [[video game developers]], [[mod (video gaming)|video game modders]], and 3D enthusiasts.<ref name=cgsociety>{{cite news |title=Mixamo Opens Technology to User-Imported Content |date=May 21, 2014 |publisher=CGSociety |url=http://www.cgsociety.org/index.php/CGSFeatures/CGSFeatureSpecial/mixamo_opens_technology_to_user_imported_content |accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref>
==History== The technology underneath Fuse was initially developed as a character creator at Stanford University<ref name=venturebeat>{{cite news |title=Mixamo debuts Fuse character creation tool on Steam using Valve’s Team Fortress 2 characters |author=Dean Takahashi |date=November 7, 2013 |publisher=Venture Beat |url=https://venturebeat.com/2013/11/07/mixamo-debuts-fuse-character-creation-tool-on-steam-using-valves-team-fortress-2-characters/ |accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref> from the work of Siddhartha Chaudhuri<ref name=stanford>{{cite web |title=3D modeling with data-driven suggestions |publisher=Stanford Digital Repository |url=http://purl.stanford.edu/vq766tr8762 |accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref> in Prof. Vladlen Koltun's group. Chaudhuri's work resulted in a [[SIGGRAPH]] publication in 2011.<ref name=cornell>{{cite web |title=Probabilistic Reasoning for Assembly-Based 3D Modeling |publisher=Cornell University |url=http://www.cs.cornell.edu/~sidch/projects/assembly/ |accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref> Mixamo also partnered with Allegorithmic in the creation of Fuse.<ref name=venturebeat/> All [[Texture mapping|texturing]] within Fuse is driven by Allegorithmic's Substance Designer.<ref name=develop>{{cite news |title=Accessible Animation |author=Craig Chapple |publisher=Develop Online |url=http://www.develop-online.net/tools-and-tech/accessible-animation/0199606 |accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref> A beta version of Fuse was originally launched on [[Steam (software)|Steam]] in November 2013.<ref name=digitalmedia/> Fuse 1.0 was officially launched in March 2014.<ref name=vizworld>{{cite news |title=Mixamo's Fuse 1.0 Launched on Valve's Steam Platform |author=Dean Meyers |date=March 27, 2014 |publisher=VizWorld |url=http://www.vizworld.com/2014/03/mixamos-fuse-1-0-launches-on-valves-steam-platform/#sthash.T9w03UC6.PhU9DXNO.dpbs |accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref>
==Software== [[File:Fuse Character Creator Carousel.png|thumb|right|Models created with Fuse.]] Fuse is a client based product that lets users choose and modify character components such as body parts in real-time.<ref name=gfxspeak>{{cite news |title=Mixamo builds out end to end products, adds upgrades in time for GDC |author=Kathleen Maher |date=March 12, 2014 |publisher=Graphic Speak |url=http://gfxspeak.com/2014/03/12/mixamo-products-upgrades/ |accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref> Users can also customize their characters with clothing and texture options provided by Allegorithmic.<ref name=gfxspeak/> Fuse's main novelty is the ability for users to import and automatically integrate their own content into the character creation system, leveraging all the features of pre-loaded content.<ref name=digitalmedia/><ref name=gamasutra/> Fuse characters are rigged through Mixamo online service. Characters have a bone driven rig and a blend shape based facial rig for [[computer facial animation|facial animation]].<ref name=develop/>
==Use and availability== Fuse is used mostly by game developers and game modders. Fuse is available on Mixamo, on the Unity Asset Store and on Steam marketplace where it has a user base of 40,000 users as of September 2014. Fuse characters can be imported through a specific series of steps into games created with the [[Source SDK]] by [[Valve Corporation|Valve]].
==License== All content available within Fuse is royalty free and regulated by the Fuse End User Licensing Agreement.<ref name=license>{{cite web|title=Fuse EULA |date=March 18, 2014 |publisher=Mixamo |url=https://www.mixamo.com/fuse/legal |accessdate=November 23, 2014 }}{{dead link|date=January 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
