== Release ==
The tagline on the cover of a VHS release titled ''Sharks'' reads, "Where sharks prey, the ocean is a bloodbath."<ref>{{cite web |title=Sharks VHS cover |url=http://snap361.net/ig-post/1491653652413636988_1646029598 |accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref>

In Italy, a VHS release was made by Avo Film.{{sfn|Gomarasca|Pulice|p=46}}

In Germany, the film was released by "VPS" on VHS titled ''Shakka - Bestie der Tiefe'' (literally: "[[Shakka (god)|Shakka]] - Beast of the Depth").<ref>{{cite web |title=OFDb - VHS: VPS (Deutschland), Freigabe: FSK 12 von Shakka - Bestie der Tiefe (1990) |url=https://ssl.ofdb.de/view.php?page=fassung&fid=5759&vid=12565 |accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref>

In the [[Czech Republic]], the film was released on [[DVD]] by "Řitka video" in 2009, under the title ''Bestie z hlubin''. The DVD contains the Czech dub and the English original version with forced Czech subtitles.<ref>[http://dvdsleuth.blogspot.com/2009/05/joe-damatos-deep-blood-on-dvd-in-czech.html dvdsleuth - Joe D'Amato's Deep Blood on DVD in Czech]</ref>

==Reception==
In 1999, Italian film critic Marco Giusti called the film a [[Z movie]] version of ''[[Jaws (film)|Jaws]]''.{{sfn|Giusti|1999|p=395}} He thought that the dialogues were slightly ridiculous, but that the small film was likable.{{sfn|Giusti|1999|p=395}}

