{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2018}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Encantadia: Pag-ibig Hanggang Wakas | show_name_2 = Avisala Encantadia: Love Until the End | image = Encantadia, Pag-ibig Hanggang Wakas title card.jpg | caption = Title card | genre = {{Plainlist| * [[Drama]] * [[Fantasy]]}} | creator = [[Suzette Doctolero]] | director = Gil Tejada Jr. | writer = {{Plainlist| * Suzette Doctolero * Joseph Balboa * Anna Aleta Nadela * Vienuel Lavina Ello}} | executive_producer = {{Plainlist| * Winnie Hollis Reyes * Mona C. Mayuga}} | starring = {{Plain list| * [[Sunshine Dizon]] * [[Iza Calzado]] * [[Karylle]] * [[Diana Zubiri]] * [[Dingdong Dantes]]}} | theme_music_composer = Allan Feliciano | opentheme = "Mahiwagang Puso" by [[Karylle]] and Jerome John Hughes | composer = Tata Betita | country = [[Philippines]] | location = Philippines | language = {{Plainlist| * [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]] * [[Enchanta]]}} | camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]] | runtime = 24-34 minutes | company = GMA Entertainment TV | network = [[GMA Network]] | picture_format = [[480i]] ([[SDTV]]) | first_aired = {{start date|2006|2|20}} | last_aired = {{end date|2006|4|28}} | num_episodes = 48 | preceded_by = ''[[Etheria]]'' | related = {{plain list| * ''[[Encantadia (2005 TV series)|Encantadia]]'' * ''[[Encantadia (2016 TV series)|Encantadia]]'' {{small|(2016)}}}} | website = http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/encantadia_pagibig_hanggang_wakas }}
'''''Encantadia: Pag-ibig Hanggang Wakas''''' (International title: ''Avisala Encantadia: Love Until the End''<ref>[http://www.igma.tv/gwi/programs/35/avisala Avisala] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120802054622/http://www.igma.tv/gwi/programs/35/avisala |date=August 2, 2012}}</ref> / {{literal translation|Encantadia: Love Until the End}}) is a 2006 [[Philippine television drama]] [[fantasy]] series broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. The series is the third instalment of the [[Encantadia]] franchise set after ''Etheria''. Directed by Gil Tejada Jr., it stars [[Sunshine Dizon]], [[Iza Calzado]], [[Karylle]], [[Diana Zubiri]] and [[Dingdong Dantes]]. It premiered on February 20, 2006 on the network's Telebabad line up replacing ''[[Etheria]]''. The series concluded on April 28, 2006 with a total of 48 episodes.<ref name="Encantadia">[[Encantadia]]. 2005. [[GMA Network]]. Retrieved on February 1, 2010.</ref><ref name="Etheria">[[Etheria]]. 2006. [[GMA Network]]. Retrieved on February 1, 2010.</ref>
The series is streaming online on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|URL=https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGRhcC_vtOrZm_qHKmF2iM9sDzkTdsATg |title=Encantadia: Pag-ibig Hanggang Wakas (Full Episodes) - YouTube |accessdate=February 16, 2018}}</ref>
==Premise== The sang’gres of Encantadia - Amihan, Pirena, Alena, and Danaya return from the past after they successfully destroyed the kingdom of Etheria. In the midst of their celebration in Sapiro, Mine-a arrives and warns the Sang’gres about an impending danger that only they can solve.<ref>{{cite web|URL=http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/encantadia_pagibig_hanggang_wakas/about/ |title=Encantadia: Pag-ibig Hanggang Wakas |accessdate=April 5, 2018}}</ref>
