[[File:Matsudonight.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Matsudo Velodrome at night]] {{nihongo|'''Matsudo Velodrome'''|松戸競輪場|Matsudo Keirinjyō}} is a [[velodrome]] located in [[Matsudo, Chiba]] that conducts [[pari-mutuel]] [[Keirin]] racing - one of [[Japan]]'s four authorized {{nihongo|"Public Sports"|公営競技|kōei kyōgi}} where [[Gambling in Japan|gambling is permitted]]. Its Keirin identification number for betting purposes is 31# (31 sharp).
Matsudo's oval is 333 meters in circumference. A typical keirin race of 2,015 meters consists of six laps around the course.
==External links== *[http://www.matsudokeirin.jp/ Matsudo Keirin Home Page (Japanese)] *[http://keirin.jp/pc/dfw/dataplaza/guest/jyoguide?KCD=31 keirin.jp Matsudo Information (Japanese)]
