{{Infobox video game | title = Pathway to Glory |image = Pathway to Glory NGAGE cover.jpg |image_size = 252px |developer = [[RedLynx]] |publisher = [[Nokia]] |designer = |engine = |released = {{vgrelease|NA|November 24, 2004|EU|November 26, 2004}} |genre = [[Turn-based tactics]] |modes = [[Single player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]], [[N-Gage Arena]] |platforms = [[Nokia N-Gage]] }}
'''''Pathway to Glory''''' is a [[turn-based tactics|tactical turn-based]] game for the [[Nokia]] [[N-Gage (device)|N-Gage]], by [[Nokia]] and [[RedLynx]], released in late 2004.
==Story== In the summer of 1943, special forces are urgently needed in the struggle for [[Europe]]. Player commands a multinational unit of highly trained men and accomplishes action-packed, historical missions by defending, ambushing, destroying and attacking.
''Pathway to Glory'' can be played in [[single-player]] and [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] mode, using either [[Hotseat (multiplayer mode)|hotseat]], [[N-Gage Arena]] or a local [[Bluetooth]] connection.
{{clear}}
