'''Plays for Young Audiences''' is the combined collection of scripts commissioned or produced by [[Seattle Children's Theatre]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Seattle Children's Theatre|url=http://www.sct.org|work=Seattle Children's Theatre website|accessdate=4 October 2011}}</ref> and the [[Children's Theatre Company]] in [[Minneapolis]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Children's Theatre Company|url=http://www.childrenstheatre.org|work=Children's Theatre Company website|accessdate=4 October 2011}}</ref> The [[children's theater]] movement developed in the [[United States]] in the 1960s, and at that time the canon of work for family audiences began to build.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Zoglin|first=Richard|title=Setting a New Stage for Kids|journal=Time|date=November 2004|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,750281,00.html|accessdate=4 October 2011}}</ref> Plays for Young Audiences began in July 2004 to provide scripts developed by Seattle Children's Theatre and the Children's Theatre Company to professional theaters, amateur/community theatres, churches, libraries and schools.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Hegman|first=Sonja|title=Partnership Fills Growing Demand for Plays for Young Audiences|journal=Dramabiz Magazine|date=January 2006|pages=34–36|url=http://www.dramabiz.com/children.htm|accessdate=4 October 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120729011751/http://www.dramabiz.com/children.htm|archivedate=29 July 2012|df=}}</ref> The mission of Plays for Young Audiences is to drive the field of [[theater]] for young people to higher levels of success<ref>{{cite journal|last=Mitchell|first=Kevin|title=The Play Publishing Landscape|journal=Stage Directions|date=April 2011|pages=14–17|issn=1047-1901|url=http://digital.turn-page.com/issue/27658|accessdate=4 October 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111023082311/http://digital.turn-page.com/issue/27658|archivedate=23 October 2011|df=}}</ref>
